# Cursor — Project Rules

This file is auto-loaded by Cursor. It tells the assistant where to start and how to navigate.

## Read first
- `CLAUDE.md` — load-bearing project rules
- `AGENTS.md` — agent-facing conventions + grep recipes
- `INDEX.md` — manifest of every per-file `.claude.md`

## ⚠️ Hard rule before ANY code edit — READ + UPDATE the sibling .claude.md

**Before** editing `<path>/<name>.{ts,tsx}` → **read** `<path>/<name>.claude.md` first.
The doc declares the file's purpose, exports, dependencies, callers, and constraints.

**After** editing, if exports / imports / business logic / auth / route / methods / i18n namespace changed,
update the sibling `.claude.md` (both the YAML frontmatter AND the matching body section) in the same change.

A stale `.claude.md` misleads the next agent. Treat it as part of the file.

Examples of where the sibling doc lives:
- `components/ui/dropdown/dropdown.tsx` → `components/ui/dropdown/dropdown.claude.md`
- `lib/server/services/category-service/category-service.ts` → `lib/server/services/category-service/category-service.claude.md`
- `app/api/products/route.ts` → `app/api/products/route.claude.md`

If the matching `.claude.md` doesn't exist, CREATE it before finishing the change.

## Naming conventions
- Files: kebab-case (`product-form.tsx`, `category-service.ts`)
- Folders: kebab-case, one per component / service / schema / etc.
- Components: PascalCase identifiers, named exports
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE
- Booleans: `is*` / `has*` / `can*`

## Where things live
- `components/ui/<name>/` — UI primitives (zero page copy)
- `components/sections/<name>/` — page sections
- `components/layout/site-header/` and `site-footer/` — site chrome (grouping folders)
- `components/sections/contact/enquiry-form/` — contact form (grouping folder)
- `app/(site)/[locale]/` — public localized routes (7 locales)
- `app/(admin)/admin/(dashboard)/` — admin routes (gated, English only)
- `app/api/` — backend route handlers
- `lib/server/services/<name>/` — business logic + prisma queries
- `lib/server/validation/<name>/` — zod schemas (API contracts)
- `lib/api-client/endpoints/<name>/` — typed axios wrappers (admin client → API)
- `messages/<locale>.json` — all translation catalogs (7 locales)
- `constants/` — typed enums, routes, site metadata
- `prisma/` — schema + migrations + seed

## Boundaries (compiler-enforced)
- `lib/server/*` starts with `'server-only'` — importing from a client component is a build error
- `lib/api-client/axios-instance.ts` starts with `'client-only'` — importing from a server component is a build error
- `lib/shared/*` is type-only, safe on both sides

## Common grep patterns
- All services: `grep -rln "kind: service" --include='*.claude.md'`
- Doc for a symbol: `grep -rln "<symbolName>" --include='*.claude.md'`
- Component using a translation namespace: `grep -rln "i18n_namespace: \"<ns>\"" --include='*.claude.md'`

## When asked to add a new component / service / schema / route
Always create the matching `.claude.md` in the same change. Folder pattern is non-negotiable.
